### MOON Language EBNF Grammar

**1. Programs and Declarations**

```ebnf
program        ::= declaration* EOF
declaration    ::= let_decl | statement

let_decl       ::= "let" IDENTIFIER ( "," IDENTIFIER )* ( "(" parameters? ")" )? 
                   ( "be" expression ( "," expression )* )? terminator
parameters     ::= IDENTIFIER ( "," IDENTIFIER )*

```

**2. Statements and Control Flow**

```ebnf
statement      ::= control_stmt | block_stmt | guarded_stmt
guarded_stmt   ::= ( show_stmt | give_stmt | set_stmt | expr_stmt ) guard_clause? terminator

guard_clause   ::= ( "if" | "unless" ) expression

show_stmt      ::= "show" expression
give_stmt      ::= "give" expression?
set_stmt       ::= "set" set_target ( "," set_target )* "to" expression ( "," expression )*
set_target     ::= IDENTIFIER ( "[" expression "]" | "." IDENTIFIER )*
expr_stmt      ::= expression

control_stmt   ::= if_stmt | unless_stmt | while_stmt | until_stmt | for_stmt
if_stmt        ::= "if" expression ( ":" block "end" | statement ) 
                   ( "else" ( if_stmt | ":" block "end" | statement ) )?
unless_stmt    ::= "unless" expression ( ":" block "end" | statement ) 
                   ( "else" ( unless_stmt | ":" block "end" | statement ) )?
while_stmt     ::= "while" expression ( ":" block "end" | statement )
until_stmt     ::= "until" expression ( ":" block "end" | statement )
for_stmt       ::= "for" "each"? IDENTIFIER "in" expression ( ":" block "end" | statement )

block_stmt     ::= "{" block "}"
block          ::= declaration*
terminator     ::= NEWLINE | EOF

```

**3. Expressions and Precedence (Lowest to Highest)**

```ebnf
expression     ::= ternary_expr
ternary_expr   ::= range_expr ( "if" expression "else" expression )*
range_expr     ::= logic_or ( "to" logic_or ( "by" logic_or )? )?

logic_or       ::= logic_and ( "or" logic_and )*
logic_and      ::= equality ( "and" equality )*
equality       ::= comparison ( ( "is" "not"? | "!=" ) comparison )*
comparison     ::= term ( ( ">" | ">=" | "<" | "<=" ) term )*

term           ::= factor ( ( "+" | "-" ) factor )*
factor         ::= unary ( ( "*" | "/" ) unary )*
unary          ::= ( "not" | "-" ) unary | call

call           ::= primary ( "(" arguments? ")" | "[" expression "]" ( "=" expression )? 
                             | "." IDENTIFIER ( "=" expression )? )*
arguments      ::= expression ( "," expression )*

primary        ::= NUMBER | STRING | IDENTIFIER | "true" | "false" | "nil" 
                   | list_literal | "(" expression ")"
list_literal   ::= "[" ( expression ( "," expression )* )? "]"

```

**4. Lexical Tokens (Terminals)**

```ebnf
NUMBER         ::= DIGIT+ ( "." DIGIT+ )?
STRING         ::= '"' [^"]* '"' | interpolated_string
IDENTIFIER     ::= ALPHA ( ALPHA | DIGIT )*
ALPHA          ::= "a" ... "z" | "A" ... "Z" | "_"
DIGIT          ::= "0" ... "9"
NEWLINE        ::= "\n"

```

*(Note: Interpolated strings (`"hi `name`!"`) are handled via state-switching in the lexical analyzer rather than strict EBNF, as standard EBNF cannot easily represent context-sensitive lexer depth).*

